value: Latin America: c Mexico to n and w SA
Secondary Forest, Second-growth Scrub (1400-3000 m; upper Tropical and Subtropical zones, in South America also Temperate Zone).

open shrubby mountain slopes & highland pastures, with scattered trees, forest edge adjoining highland scrub, landslide scars, streams, hedgerows, second growth, coffee plantations;mostly 1200-3000m, outside breeding season to 500-1000m
